"{\"uid\": \"news18.com-olympics-paris-olympics-2024-manu-bhaker-clinches-historic-bronze-in-womens-10m-air-pistol-brings-indias-first-medal-in-paris-8981589.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"History is made, as India's Manu Bhaker brought home the nation's first medal of the 2024 Paris Olympics, clinching a bronze medal in the 10m Air Pistol Final on Sunday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9985284362561302, \"rank\": 0.0014188262806065141, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 28, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manu Bhaker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Manu Bhaker finished her run after 22 shots, scoring 221.7, falling just 0.1 short of overthrowing second placed Yeji Kim in the penultimate series.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 171, \"end\": 182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manu Bhaker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\"}, {\"begin\": 284, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2653099233000681e-11, \"text\": \"Yeji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\"}, {\"begin\": 289, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.9503334092225885, \"rank\": 0.049251111674190225, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With her bronze, 22-year-old Bhaker broke India's 12-year Olympic medal drought in Shooting, and also became the first female shooter to win a medal in the same event for India.\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9985284362561302, \"rank\": 0.0014188262806065141, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9985284362561302, \"rank\": 0.0014188262806065141, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bhaker started off the first series with her eyes on the prize scoring a strong 50.2 off her five shots, to skyrocket herself up to second place out of the gate, right behind South Korea's Ye Jin Oh, who scored an impressive 52.2.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Indian kept her composure and almost recreate her first series exactly with her next five shots, scoring 50.1 in the Series 2, and putting up a total of 100.3.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9946592217885765, \"rank\": 0.005132296923475568, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, South Korea's Ye Jin Oh and Kim Yeji both overtook Bhaker, pushing her to third place by the end of the five-shot series.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A battle ensued withing the top three, as they went shot-for shot, with Bhaker, Ye Jin and Kim all shuffling places throughout Stage 2, where Single Shots ensued.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanye_West\", \"score\": 0.9999999990679953, \"rank\": 9.279402556578088e-10, \"text\": \"Ye\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanye_West\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanye_West\"}, {\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jin-Soo_Kwon\", \"score\": 0.5450931922395141, \"rank\": 0.8343844249738821, \"text\": \"Jin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jin-Soo_Kwon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jin-Soo_Kwon\"}, {\"begin\": 1116, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.9503334092225885, \"rank\": 0.049251111674190225, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a thrilling shot 21, after securing a medal finish, Bhaker overtook Kim Yeji by 0.1 points, but Yeji overtook her with the 22nd shot to pull one over her and creep up to second by yet another 0.1 points.\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1263,